## Current Filter Logic (CommandBar.astro lines 307-347)
The filter command selects '.card' elements and checks child text:
```javascript
cards.forEach(function(el) {
  const title = el.querySelector('.card__title')?.textContent || '';
  const desc = el.querySelector('.card__desc')?.textContent || '';
  const tags = el.querySelector('.card__tags')?.textContent || '';
  const text = (title + ' ' + desc + ' ' + tags).toLowerCase();
  if (text.includes(keyword)) {
    el.classList.add('cmd-highlight');
    matchCount++;
  } else {
    el.classList.add('cmd-dim');
  }
});
```

## Updated Logic
Change the card filtering to prefer data-filter-text when available:
```javascript
cards.forEach(function(el) {
  const filterAttr = el.getAttribute('data-filter-text');
  var text;
  if (filterAttr) {
    text = filterAttr.toLowerCase();
  } else {
    const title = el.querySelector('.card__title')?.textContent || '';
    const desc = el.querySelector('.card__desc')?.textContent || '';
    const tags = el.querySelector('.card__tags')?.textContent || '';
    text = (title + ' ' + desc + ' ' + tags).toLowerCase();
  }
  if (text.includes(keyword)) {
    el.classList.add('cmd-highlight');
    matchCount++;
  } else {
    el.classList.add('cmd-dim');
  }
});
```

This is a small, surgical change. Only modify the cards.forEach block.

